1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">here=E2=80=99s a Telegraph story about Revolut</a>:</p><blockq=
uote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The banking app, which is not a licensed =
bank, is asking suspected fraud victims to take selfies while holding up a =
piece of paper that says they understand they are =E2=80=9Cunlikely=E2=80=
=9D to get their money back.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The app requir=
es customers to go through the security checks when it suspects they could =
be the victim of a scam.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It uses this inter=
vention, Revolut said, to =E2=80=9Cbreak the spell=E2=80=9D of a potential =
scammer.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the selfies were described as =
=E2=80=9Chorrible=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Clike hostage photos=E2=80=9D by sol=
icitors who represented scam victims.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">I gather that if you tell Revolut to send your money to a scammer, =
and Revolut notices, it says =E2=80=9Cyou are being scammed, are you sure?,=
=E2=80=9D and if you say =E2=80=9Cyes=E2=80=9D then they make you send the =
selfie before they will send the money. I=E2=80=99m kind of with Revolut he=
re, but on the other hand, if they=E2=80=99re so sure it=E2=80=99s a scam m=
aybe they should just not allow the transfer? Even if the customer sends th=
e selfie? Perhaps you want a hard block here.</p><table class=3D"header" wi=
