</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2021, Damien Hirst offered art coll=
ectors a proposition that was=C2=A0very 2021 and very Damien Hirst:</p><ol =
style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Hirst had made 10,000 paintings of =E2=80=
=9Ccolourful hand-painted dots on A4 paper,=E2=80=9D as <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35465286.256336/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZ=
3VhcmRpYW4uY29tL2FydGFuZGRlc2lnbi9hcnRpY2xlLzIwMjQvbWF5LzIyL2RhbWllbi1oaXJz=
dC1hcnR3b3Jrcy1wYWludGVkLXllYXJzLWxhdGVyLWN1cnJlbmN5LWFydGlzdA/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBff1b4f59" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;">today=E2=80=99s story in the Guardian</a>=C2=
=A0puts it, and he was offering them for sale, but with a twist.</li>=09<li=
 style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The twist was that you could buy a nonfungib=
le token (NFT), on the blockchain, corresponding to one of those dot painti=
ngs.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Then Hirst would light your p=
ainting on fire, and you=E2=80=99d get to keep the NFT.</li>=09<li style=3D=
"margin-bottom: 5px;"><em>Or</em>, or, or, you could keep the painting, but=
 then you would lose the NFT.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=
=9CIn total, buyers chose to retain the physical versions of 5,149 painting=
s=E2=80=9D; almost 4,000 buyers chose the fire and the NFT. (=E2=80=9CHirst=
 kept 1,000 of the works, although he opted to hold them as the NFT version=
s,=E2=80=9D says the Guardian.)=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anywa=
y Hirst obviously did not bother putting all the dots on all 10,000 papers;=
 there was a factory:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According=
 to sources familiar with the production of The Currency series, dozens of =
artists were hired to assist with the factory-style production of the paint=
ings in 2018 and 2019. Some worked eight-hour days for several months, wear=
ing cumbersome masks to protect from the paint fumes. ...</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">Lawyers for Hirst and Science said they always adhered to re=
levant health and safety rules and practices.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">Sure. But the news today is:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">The initial sale brought in about $18m. At the time, Hirst sa=
id of the project: =E2=80=9CIt comprises of 10,000 NFTs, each corresponding=
 to a unique physical artwork made in 2016.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">The paintings were sold via a single authorised seller, Heni, run=
 by Hirst=E2=80=99s business manager. It said at the time that the works we=
re =E2=80=9Ccreated by hand in 2016=E2=80=9D.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">However, five sources familiar with the creation of the works, inc=
luding some of the painters who put the dots to paper, told the Guardian ma=
ny of them were mass-produced in 2018 and 2019.</p></blockquote><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">I gather that early-career Damien Hirst works are worth m=
ore than later-career Damien Hirst factory products, though I am not sure w=
hy the difference between 2016 and 2019 would matter all that much. Surely =
no one was expecting that Hirst himself put all the dots on all the papers;=
 surely, when you pay for a Damien Hirst painting, part of what you are pay=
ing for is, like, the joke that Hirst is making about the mass production a=
nd commercialization of art.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But here=
 specifically you were paying for the joke he was making about the blockcha=
in! He was gonna burn the paintings! Imagine being angry that you paid Dami=
en Hirst to burn a painting that his factory made in 2016, but then you fou=
nd out that he actually burned a painting that his factory made in 2019.</p=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Honestly this makes me like Hirst more. I thi=
nk this is the first good joke that I=E2=80=99ve ever seen in the <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35465286.256336/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL25ld3NsZXR0ZXJzLzIwMjEtMDktMTAvbW9uZXktc3R1=
ZmYtZnVuZ2libGUtc2xpY2VzLW9mLW5vbi1mdW5naWJsZS10b2tlbnM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUyMjI=
0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3=
Rlcm09MjQwNTIyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf01=
b457b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">=E2=80=9Cobject-fire-token-money=E2=80=9D NFT genre</a>? In =
particular, it is a sophisticated=C2=A0<em>blockchain=C2=A0</em>joke. The b=
lockchain, of course, is a tamper-proof=C2=A0record of provenance. Whatever=
 bad things you can say about NFTs, one thing that is surely true of an NFT=
 is that you can tell when it was created. The creation date of these NFTs =
=E2=80=94=C2=A02021, of course! =E2=80=94=C2=A0is permanently and immutably=
 inscribed in the blockchain. The paintings=E2=80=99 creation date, man, wh=
o knows; he burned those. You=C2=A0<em>can=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>backdate the=
 creation of a crypto artwork; immutable provable time sequencing is in som=
e deep sense the=C2=A0<em>point=C2=A0</em>of crypto. But Hirst found a way =
to do it.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacin=
